The paper deals with image restoration tasks such as super-resolution and denoising, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper proposes a new technique for regularization of deep learning models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of frequency analysis, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IT.
